# EFZ-Prüfungsvorbereitung – Implementation Plan

A full-stack PWA for Swiss commercial apprenticeship (Kaufleute EFZ) exam preparation, featuring quizzes, timed exams, flashcards, progress tracking, and admin tools.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope & Delivery Strategy**: This is a large application. I'll build a fully functional MVP with all core features, but some content (1000+ questions) will be represented by a solid seed dataset of ~250 representative questions with the infrastructure to easily add more. The architecture supports all requested features from day one.

> [!WARNING]
> **MongoDB**: You'll need a MongoDB Atlas free-tier connection string. I'll use a `.env` file for configuration. Do you already have a MongoDB Atlas cluster, or should the app include instructions for creating one?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Stripe**: Requires a Stripe account + API keys. I'll wire up the full payment flow but it will use test keys. Do you have Stripe keys, or should I include placeholder setup?

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Frontend["Frontend (Vite + React)"]
        A[React SPA] --> B[React Router]
        B --> C[Auth Pages]
        B --> D[Dashboard]
        B --> E[Quiz/Exam/Flashcards]
        B --> F[Progress Tracker]
        B --> G[Admin Panel]
        B --> H[Tips Section]
    end
    subgraph Backend["Backend (Express + Node.js)"]
        I[Auth API] --> J[JWT + bcrypt]
        K[Questions API] --> L[CRUD + filtering]
        M[Sessions API] --> N[Quiz/Exam logic]
        O[Progress API] --> P[Stats aggregation]
        Q[Payment API] --> R[Stripe]
    end
    Frontend -->|REST API| Backend
    Backend --> S[(MongoDB Atlas)]
```

**Stack**: Vite + React 18 (frontend), Express 5 (backend), MongoDB + Mongoose, JWT auth, Stripe, Workbox PWA.

